1
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:17,480
[Hello,]

2
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,080
[this is the hotel housekeeping.]

3
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,680
[A guest from room 6804]

4
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:22,880
[accidentally left a chessboard on the tray.]

5
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,800
[Could it have been delivered to your room by mistake?]

6
00:00:32,159 --> 00:00:33,680
6804?

7
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,040
That last move, the third line, third column,

8
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,240
I think I was too careless.

9
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:46,760
Or maybe,

10
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:47,680
you did it on purpose.

11
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:51,600
In a game of chess,

12
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:54,160
you always need a bit of a hook

13
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:55,440
to lure others into the game.

14
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,160
Your style

15
00:00:58,160 --> 00:00:59,480
is quite bold.

16
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,000
Life is like a game of chess.

17
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,720
That's true.

18
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:06,080
Indeed,

19
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:08,520
your style of playing chess is rather cold.

20
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:10,800
But you also chose to attack proactively.

21
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,160
Come to 6804 to find me.

22
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,320
The game is exciting.

23
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,080
It's worth coming.

24
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:20,920
Mr. He.

25
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:22,360
Thank you for letting me win.

26
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,600
[Who are you?]

27
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:29,920
How about

28
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,000
having a drink with me?

29
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,520
Mr. He,

30
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:36,400
playing chess is tiring.

31
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,320
I'm tired.

32
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,080
Ms. Ye,

33
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:43,640
thanks to you,

34
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,400
look,

35
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,400
I bought that

36
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,760
Cubist painting

37
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,920
I bought it without hesitation.

38
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:50,600
My dad praised me

39
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,000
for my improved taste.

40
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,880
Ms. Ye,

41
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,720
do you have any new paintings

42
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,320
to recommend to me?

43
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:01,080
Let's wait a bit, Mr. Zhang.

44
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,360
Artworks

45
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,960
also need the right timing.

46
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,000
Isn't that He Xiaochen?

47
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,520
Work is too busy.

48
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,360
Always interrupts my chess chat.

49
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,040
Wait a moment,

50
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:29,920
I'll go say hello.

51
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,400
Mr. Ye,

52
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,120
I was just talking to Mr. He

53
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,360
about the Times Gallery.

54
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,320
Well,

55
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:39,880
I'll go say hello.

56
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,360
Not now.

57
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,320
Mr. He

58
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,280
doesn't like to deal with strangers,

59
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,400
but he told me

60
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,160
that his father mentioned

61
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:50,200
that your creative talent is very impressive.

62
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,440
He knows me?

63
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,880
Then I'll go back to He now.

64
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:55,640
Let's talk later.

65
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,400
Okay.

66
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,440
Finished?

67
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:03,400
That was

68
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,840
the manager of the Times Gallery,

69
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,920
Ye Zhiqu.

70
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,360
I also do curating,

71
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,640
so we're kind of colleagues.

72
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,200
I don't care about your career.

73
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,720
Let's get back to that move.

74
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,680
Keep an eye on He Xiaochen.

75
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,760
During the three days of the competition at the Black Gold Hotel,

76
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,680
don't let Ye Zhiqu come into contact with him.

77
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,480
Understood.

78
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,880
He Xiaochen is indeed, as the rumors say,

79
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,280
a strange person.

80
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,960
But he is really smart.

81
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,480
We just need to use his identity

82
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,720
at the critical juncture

83
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,360
to lure Ye Zhiqu into the game.

84
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:38,680
You should also try to

85
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,320
[appear in Room 6804.]

86
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,160
[It's not safe.]

87
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,600
Are you okay?

88
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,440
A year ago,

89
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,000
Zhen Shida's men hunted me and Hao Feng.

90
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,839
I still can't remember

91
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,560
the car accident.

92
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,600
You were badly injured.

93
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,720
When I got to the scene,

94
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,520
I only had time to save you.

95
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,320
But my brother

96
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,760
was taken away by Zhen Shida's men.

97
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,800
He couldn't escape,

98
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:35,040
and became a scapegoat.

99
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,400
You told me

100
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,360
that Hao Feng was my best friend.

101
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,840
But I can't remember anything.

102
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,960
Jia Yu,

103
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:58,880
don't force yourself.

104
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,200
You just need to remember Hao Feng's revenge,

105
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
and why we are here,

106
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,720
and why we do this.

107
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,960
What do you think, Mr. Zhang?

108
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,720
Don't be shy.

109
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,880
share your thoughts.

110
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,120
If you ask me,

111
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:30,800
this painting,

112
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,200
I could've done it when I was five.

113
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,920
It's so elementary.

114
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:38,720
Yeah,

115
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,600
this is from a friend

116
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,000
who just started painting.

117
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,360
It's a bit immature.

118
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:43,960
See?

119
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:44,880
I told you,

120
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,880
I have a sharp eye.

121
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,360
I grew up

122
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:49,000
in a sophisticated environment.

123
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,800
I only appreciate expert paintings.

124
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,880
This one is somewhat interesting.

125
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,400
The color blocks are bold.

126
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,080
But this level of work

127
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:00,600
is still not good enough for me.

128
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,960
It's far from the works of a master.

129
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,200
In that case,

130
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:06,960
since you don't appreciate

131
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,280
any of the paintings here,

132
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,040
when I have

133
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,200
I have some good paintings here,

134
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,320
I'll definitely invite you.

135
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,000
Okay?

136
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,120
Okay.

137
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,480
I have friends coming later.

138
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,280
Excuse me.

139
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,680
Okay.

140
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,760
See you later.

141
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:18,560
Bye.

142
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,760
Young and hot-blooded,

143
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,080
yet appropriately arrogant.

144
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,400
You're here.

145
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,120
I saw the door wasn't locked,

146
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,200
so I didn't want to disturb

147
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,720
your painting appreciation.

148
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,120
These are some paintings by my friends.

149
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,640
They're a bit of a mess.

150
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,440
I didn't expect

151
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,840
you to be so complimentary.

152
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,000
A mess?

153
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,920
I don't think so.

154
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,200
Look at this.

155
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,360
The colors are bold,

156
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,000
and he managed to

157
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,280
the stiff blue next to it

158
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,560
come to life.

159
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,360
Your friend

160
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,000
may be unconventional,

161
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,480
but he has real talent.

162
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,320
To be honest,

163
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,520
these paintings

164
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,480
are just some casual scribbles

165
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,720
I did in my spare time.

166
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,640
I'm truly sorry.

167
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,240
I may have been a bit inappropriate earlier.

168
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,280
Please forgive me.

169
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,520
It's okay.

170
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,560
At least it shows you understand art.

171
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,080
It's a shame though,

172
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,360
in our line of work,

173
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,840
besides ability,

174
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:35,920
what everyone values most are

175
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,200
education and fame.

176
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,560
When I was young,

177
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,080
relying on my own ideas,

178
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:42,280
I was rejected by rules and fame,

179
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,440
shut out from the door.

180
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,240
In the past couple of years,

181
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,640
I've become the manager.

182
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:47,720
Please, have a seat.

183
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,880
So you're willing to accept and trust me

184
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:56,560
because we both

185
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,920
have similar experiences.

186
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,840
Would you

187
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,120
be willing to give me one of your paintings?

188
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,640
Sure.

189
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:05,960
They're just some

190
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,080
unnoticed works.

191
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,200
Don't say that.

192
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,680
The new exhibition hall

193
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,320
new exhibition hall,

194
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,280
the space and lighting design

195
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,640
are very good.

196
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,480
He's

197
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,760
most value

198
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,200
fame and education.

199
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,880
He never sticks to empty fame.

200
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,800
He told me

201
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,280
if your paintings

202
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,480
could be exhibited at the same time,

203
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,000
it would be even better.

204
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,159
Really?

205
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,280
My paintings can also be exhibited?

206
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:41,559
Of course.

207
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,679
I told you before.

208
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:45,960
Even our Mr. He

209
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:48,000
is very impressed

210
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,880
by your young works.

211
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,760
The Times Gallery has been

212
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,080
managed by me for years.

213
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,120
If

214
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,960
I talk to Mr. Zhen,

215
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,640
maybe we can make it happen.

216
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:02,640
That's great.

217
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,480
But there's one painting

218
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,120
that might not be able to be exhibited.

219
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,600
Which one?

220
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,160
The one with the highest estimated value in the gallery,

221
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,160
Disappearing Rose.
